Date: Sun, 10 May 2026 20:40:22 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 11/15] notifications: return ASK instead of DENIED when
 service unavailable

When the notification service is not available (headless mode), return
ASK status instead of DENIED from both the renderer and browser side.
Maps Notification.permission to 'default' instead of 'denied'.

diff --git a/content/browser/notifications/blink_notification_service_impl.cc b/content/browser/notifications/blink_notification_service_impl.cc
index 2fd342198d..05fcb89f83 100644
--- a/content/browser/notifications/blink_notification_service_impl.cc
+++ b/content/browser/notifications/blink_notification_service_impl.cc
@@ -126,7 +126,7 @@ void BlinkNotificationServiceImpl::GetPermissionStatus(
   DCHECK_CURRENTLY_ON(BrowserThread::UI);
   if (!browser_context_ ||
       !browser_context_->GetPlatformNotificationService()) {
-    std::move(callback).Run(blink::mojom::PermissionStatus::DENIED);
+    std::move(callback).Run(blink::mojom::PermissionStatus::ASK);
     return;
   }
 
